out the window -- and with it goes responsibility for one's acts.
Somehow I have trouble reconciling that with what we know of
Tolkien's world view.

But I've just now been struck by a possible way out of the dilemma.

Suppose we think of the Music in a similar way to the laws of
physics. We do not see any conflict between free will and the fact
that I cannot choose to levitate.

So what would the music or Fate consist of? How would it govern Ainur
and Elves but not Men?

Is it as simple as this: that the Ainur and the Elves are constrained
by their nature to remain within Arda for all of its days, while Men
are not so constrained? That seems almost too simple, but at least it
preserves free will.

